url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-06-27T08:50:53Z","updated_at":"2020-06-27T08:50:53Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"@willmcgugan Thanks it's working now. But I wanted to use that for windows legacy terminal but it wasn't working so I tried that on Jupyter. I want to use Table on legacy windows. Can you recommend the box style that will surely work on cmd? I guess box.ASCII can be an option but  I'm open for other suggestions.","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/650535690","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/125#issuecomment-650535690","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/125","id":650535690,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY1MDUzNTY5MA==","user":{"login":"willmcgugan","id":554369,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1NDM2OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/554369?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-06-27T10:06:41Z","updated_at":"2020-06-27T10:06:41Z","author_association":"OWNER","body":"Most of the unicode box characters don't render on windows legacy. Any of the heavy / double / rounded characters display as question marks. Rather than have a situation where a table looks good on OSX / Linux / Window Terminal but garbage on Windows legacy, I set the box parameter to `box.SQUARE` on Windows legacy.\r\n\r\nBut that does mean you can't select `box.ASCII` or one of the other box constants that would work on cmd.exe. So perhaps the solution would be to only substitute the box constants that are known not to work on Windows legacy.","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/650544568","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/125#issuecomment-650544568","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/125","id":650544568,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY1MDU0NDU2OA==","user":{"login":"willmcgugan","id":554369,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1NDM2OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/554369?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-06-27T11:08:34Z","updated_at":"2020-06-27T11:08:34Z","author_association":"OWNER","body":"Did some more digging, and it turns out that it's not cmd.exe that doesn't support box characters, its the choice of font. The raster fonts are missing some box characters, but the truetype fonts look fine.\r\n\r\nIt's a bit of a dilemma. There is no way to detect the user's choice of font. I'll need to think about that one, but it does look like I can support a greater range of box characters on Windows in a future update. ","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/650557064","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/125#issuecomment-650557064","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/125","id":650557064,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY1MDU1NzA2NA==","user":{"login":"SinghHrmn","id":29910324,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5OTEwMzI0","avatar_url":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/29910324?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn","html_url":"https://github.com/SinghHrmn","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SinghHrmn/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-06-27T12:47:45Z","updated_at":"2020-06-27T12:47:45Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"Actually I was testing that on github actions and clearly windows on GitHub Actions don't support unicode. My application is basically cross platform and I need to check if my build pass on both the system. But I don't want to drop the beautiful table on windows where users have terminal that support unicode. So I'm handling that with a try except block that, if I can write and I don't get UnicodeEncode error I can print the unicode table but if I can't I'll switch table to use box.ASCII which is supported by CI. Do you have any other better implementation ?","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/650567210","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/125#issuecomment-650567210","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/125","id":650567210,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY1MDU2NzIxMA==","user":{"login":"willmcgugan","id":554369,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1NDM2OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/554369?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-06-27T14:22:33Z","updated_at":"2020-06-27T14:22:33Z","author_association":"OWNER","body":"Github Actions should support unicode output, but I think you will need to set the [PYTHONIOENCODING](https://docs.python.org/3/using/cmdline.html#envvar-PYTHONIOENCODING) environment variable to \"utf-8\".\r\n\r\nAs far as tests goes, you might want to set `legacy_windows=False` on the Console constructor, so the output is the same on all platforms.\r\n\r\nI think perhaps the solution to box characters on windows is to set a different default for Windows, but allow that to be modified in the Table constructor. ","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/650764729","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/125#issuecomment-650764729","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/125","id":650764729,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY1MDc2NDcyOQ==","user":{"login":"willmcgugan","id":554369,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1NDM2OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/554369?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-06-28T14:04:06Z","updated_at":"2020-06-28T14:04:06Z","author_association":"OWNER","body":"Version 3.0.0 has support for more box characters on legacy Windows. By default it will substitute any unsafe box characters, but you can override this with a new `safe_box` boolean.\r\n\r\nRun the following to see how the box constants render:\r\n\r\n```\r\npython -m rich.box\r\n```\r\n\r\nNot sure if that helps your testing scenario.","performed_via_github_app":null}]